# TypeScript Standards

## Interface Definition

All interfaces must extend appropriate HTML attributes and use VariantProps:

```typescript
export interface ButtonProps
  extends ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>,
    VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {
  /** Custom CSS class name */
  className?: string;
  /** Button size variant */
  $size?: ButtonSize;
  /** Show loading state with spinner */
  $loading?: boolean;
  /** Loading text to display when loading is true */
  $loadingText?: string;
  /** Make the button full width */
  $fullWidth?: boolean;
  /** Render as a different element when true */
  $asChild?: boolean;
  /** Element type to render when asChild is true */
  $as?: ElementType;
}
```

## Type Exports

Export all types for external usage:

```typescript
export type ButtonVariant = 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'destructive';
export type ButtonSize = 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
export type ButtonMode = 'default' | 'icon' | 'alternative';
```

## Props with $ Prefix

All custom props MUST use the `$` prefix:

```typescript
interface ComponentProps {
  $variant?: ComponentVariant; // ✅ Correct
  $size?: ComponentSize; // ✅ Correct
  $loading?: boolean; // ✅ Correct
  className?: string; // ✅ Correct
  variant?: string; // ❌ Wrong - conflicts with HTML
  size?: string; // ❌ Wrong - conflicts with HTML
}
```

## Generic Types

Use generic types for polymorphic components:

```typescript
interface PolymorphicProps<T extends ElementType = 'div'> {
  $as?: T;
  children?: React.ReactNode;
}

type ComponentProps<T extends ElementType = 'div'> = PolymorphicProps<T> &
  Omit<React.ComponentPropsWithoutRef<T>, keyof PolymorphicProps<T>>;
```

## JSDoc Comments

Document all public interfaces:

````typescript
/**
 * Button component for user interactions
 *
 * @example
 * ```tsx
 * <Button $variant="primary" $size="md">
 *   Click me
 * </Button>
 * ```
 */
export const Button = ({ ... }) => {
  // Component implementation
};
````
